FAM20A golgi associated secretory pathway pseudokinase

definition.value: A rare, multisystem disorder, characterized by neurogenic arthrogryposis multiplex congenita, renal tubular dysfunction and neonatal cholestasis with low serum gamma-glutamyl transferase activity.

A rare, syndromic genetic deafness disease characterized by symmetric or asymmetric knuckle pads (typically located on the distal and interphalangeal joints), leukonychia, diffuse palmoplantar keratoderma, and congenital, mild to moderate sensorineural deafness.

label.value: Median nodule of the upper lip

definition.value: A rare familial facial anomaly characterized by a nodule beneath the vermilion border of the upper lip that tapered into the frenulum. The lesion is soft, easily compressible and asymptomatic. It can be wide (up to 8 mm) or flat and less prominent. Regression of the nodule by age has been reported. There have been no further descriptions in the literature since 1994.

Vitamin B12-unresponsive methylmalonic acidemia is an inborn error of vitamin B12 (cobalamin) metabolism characterized by recurrent ketoacidotic crises or transient vomiting, dehydration, hypotonia and intellectual deficit, which does not respond to administration of vitamin B12. There are two types of vitamin B12-unresponsive methylmalonic acidemia: mut0 and mut- (see these terms).
A rare, adult-onset, progressive myopathy characterized by progressive eyelid ptosis, ophthalmoplegia, dysphagia, dysarthria and proximal limb weakness.
Noma is a gangrenous disease that causes severe destruction of the soft and osseous tissues of the face.

Noonan syndrome-like disorder with loose anagen hair

definition.value: A Noonan-related syndrome, characterized by facial anomalies suggestive of Noonan syndrome, loose anagen hair, frequent congenital heart defects, distinctive skin features (darkly pigmented skin, keratosis pilaris, eczema or ichtyosis), and short stature that is often associated with a growth hormone deficiency. Psychomotor delay with attention deficit/hyperactivity disorder (ADHD) is frequently observed.

label.value: GIPC PDZ domain containing family member 3

definition.value: A rare developmental defect during embryogenesis syndrome characterized by a glabellar capillary malformation, congenital communicating hydrocephalus, and posterior fossa brain abnormalities, including Dandy-Walker malformation, cerebellar vermis agenesis, and mega cisterna magna. Seizures are occasionally associated. There have been no further descriptions in the literature since 1979.

label.value: FYVE and coiled-coil domain autophagy adaptor 1

definition.value: A rare syndromic urinary tract malformation characterized by the association of severe voiding dysfunction and inversion of facial expression when the child smiles or cries.

sperm antigen with calponin homology and coiled-coil domains 1 like

definition.value: A rare, genetic, syndromic intellectual disability characterized by severe intellectual disability, distinctive craniofacial features and variable multiple congenital anomalies including ocular, brain, urogenital and skeletal abnormalities.
